The paper focuses on the design of a deep learning system for face verification/recognition, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The use of Deep Convolutional Neural Networks (DCNNs) is a key aspect of the paper, which also makes it relevant to multimedia (cs.MM) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper discusses some open issues regarding DCNNs for object recognition problems, which could also place it under information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category.
